| tenant_token   | Tenant JWT   |

---

## ğŸ”„ Typical Flow

1. Platform user registers and logs in
2. Platform user creates a tenant
3. Tenant users sign up and log in
4. Admin creates services
5. Users check availability
6. Users create bookings
7. Optional payment initiation

---

## ğŸ“¦ API Modules

### Platform Auth

* `POST /api/platform/auth/signup`
* `POST /api/platform/auth/login`

### Tenant Management

* `POST /api/platform/tenant/register`

### Tenant Auth

* `POST /api/{company}/auth/signup`
* `POST /api/{company}/auth/login`

### Admin (Tenant)

* `POST /api/{company}/admin/services`
* `PATCH /api/{company}/admin/services/:id`
* `GET /api/{company}/admin/services`
* `DELETE /api/{company}/admin/services/:id`

### User APIs

* `GET /api/{company}/users`
* `GET /api/{company}/users/availability/:serviceId`
* `POST /api/{company}/users/bookings/:serviceId`

---

## âš™ï¸ Booking Logic

* Availability is calculated dynamically based on:

  * Service duration
  * Capacity
  * Existing bookings
* Prevents overlapping bookings
* Supports quantity-based booking for capacity-based services

